annotation.TEXT: Gulp!
Oh, and there's this thing I've got to deal with. One moment please...
NO!!! I wanted the cape from that superSomeGuy712x!
Now, you saw me pass some pipes back there, right? Well, one of them can be entered. However, I don't want to do so just yet...
Multi kill!
Hyper Zone?
Oh, man! I'm hurting badly here!
On top of that, some Yoshi coins, which would've prevented that last Yoshi coin in the main area from appearing if I had raided this place first.
Alright, I'm done here! Now let's head to the next level!
Demo count: -1.$
Ever have one of those days, where you feel like you can't stop making mistakes?
There's a couple more SomeGuy712xes (or is it SomeGuy712xs... I'm not sure how to pluralize that one) over here. Do whatever to them and move on.
I'll take the cape again, thank you very much.

Now, once again, I could go and loot this place, but I'm just going leave early again, without getting any more Yoshi coins, so I can replay the level the regular way, with all of the Yoshi coins present there.
And of course, this counts as the normal exit and unlocks the next level, but as I just said, I'm going to go back and replay this level the normal way.
Guess what's going to be on the other side of that pipe. Also, let's hope I can stay alive until I reach said pipe...
Lots of coins to get here. Just watch out for superSomeGuy712xes.
Ooh, bouncy!
Ult- D'oh!
Ehh, I'll let you live this time, goomba.
Okay, now I want to backtrack for another cape...
Yes, got it!

Alright, so we've got this automatic scrolling here, along with munchers and the occasional SomeGuy712x or other bad guy, often breaking out of turn blocks. (Yeah, they're called "SomeGuy712x" this time!)
Now this half Yoshi coin makes the block below it invisible, so I would imagine that block would hold an item (like the ones in the ghost house did), but I don't know any way of hitting that block.
Okay, I've gotten Yoshi coin number four, so now, let's go back to the enterable pipe that I skipped before.
Well, they're all flowers, so there you go.
ARGH! NO! I won't let you superSomeGuy712xes stop me this time!
...but only from below.
Also, MOOOONNN!!! And also, don't worry about screwing up the level by hitting the flower blocks first. They'll still give you the keys and "balloon" after collecting the half Yoshi coins regardless.
Okay, I'm going to want to grab this SomeGuy712x's shell and hold onto it for later.
No, not that Hyper Zone!
Now, Yoshi can protect you from the munchers, provided you don't run into the side of them like I just did! But, that's not the main reason I brought Yoshi here.
Now, one other thing I thought of trying with the balloon was going down and left under the level, but...
However, this doesn't seem to be all that beneficial...
You can liberate this superSomeGuy712x of his cape.

Okay, that should be good enough. If you've collected at least 30 coins total in this level and brought a SomeGuy712x shell with you, you can get a 1-up from this star block under the fifth Yoshi coin!

Okay, now this is why I brought Yoshi. After you grab this half Yoshi coin, it'll make the block below it invisible like usual, and this invisible block holds wings! So, if you're fast, and maybe use Yoshi's tongue, you can grab them! No block cloning required!
Double kill!
And now for a pointless block clone for a pointless key, that you probably can't grab without trapping yourself.
...only to lose Yoshi! Dang it!
Awesome! And they take you to the same bonus area as they did the last two times. This is an easy way to get a blue Yoshi.
Hmm... Maybe I'll try coming back with a cape later and do some TAS-ed flying to see if there's anything further this way.
Gotta check every pipe, even the ends that don't look like they'd be enterable.
There are munchers to the right of the exit pipe, but they're not guarding anything of value, so just ignore them.
Okay, now this pipe can be entered...
Yes, I agree that this hack is Definetele one of th3 b3st hacks around here and there and the world
Whoops, already read you. Yeah, yeah, Iam sure you'll get help with your homework soon...
Okay, now can I get 50 stars twice in a row? That'd be so awesome...
Alright, let's resume the main quest now! Oh, and off camera, I picked up another Yoshi from topp of the secret. There's a very good reason why, as you'll see soon.
Aw, man... I can't hit the invisible block that way? Wait, let me try again...
Too many close calls! Come on, pull it together, SomeGuy712x! Don't let these superSomeGuy712xes get the better of you!
...And then I got hit in some silly way...
Psyche! Double kill!
Wow, I am just getting massacred here!
Mega kill!
That was kind of cool.
ARGH!!! Should've done a barrel roll...
D'OH!!!
Hi, Yoshi!
Ooh, roulette block item! Perfect timing! I could use a cape!
Nuts. Well, at least I'm finally through that superSomeGuy712x infested place...

After that, demolish the rest of the dudes over here. Also, these star blocks can't be opened at all, not even by flying underneath with a blue Yoshi. (I've tried to before, and I either get squished against the left edge of the screen before I can get low enough to pass underneath, or I go too low and just die.)
Now that I have a blue Yoshi, I can eat a SomeGuy712x and fly!
...I can't really move fast enough for this to be at all useful... If only there was a trick similar to the left+right glitch, but to allow you to move left quickly instead of right.
Okay, I'm going to try something with this shell here and see if it works...
Demo count: 15
Watch out for the superSomeGuy712x quartet here.
Totally awesome!
WAHH! Get back here, Yoshi!
Nope, definitely can't hit that block that way. I can certainly kill myself though!
Man, I'm getting sloppy here. Good thing there's a green block for me to get a cape back from.
Well, I'd better keep playhing until I reach the castel with a boss hope I don't fear

Now, over here is a setup that's just like in the original's Butter Bridge 1. There's a feather in the ? block, and a few multi-coin blocks hidden among the turn blocks. Try to collect at least some of the possible coins from them, but don't risk your life.
Fish. Goomba. Yada yada.
Mistimed the B button there, so I'll just wait for it to come around again. Aim carefully...
Yelloh heaven zone, here we go!
Hey there, little SomeGuy712x. Want your shell back? Okay, here you go.
Really? Wow... All this time I thought it was filled with numbers!

Hello, and welcome to yet another exciting episode of Chaos CompleXX! I'm back in this ghost house again, because, for some strange reason, I forgot to show you guys what's in these ? blocks before the half Yoshi coins are grabbed.
Okay, these green pipes can't be entered at all.
Alright, that unlocks a boss level. What kinds of evil traps await inside? Find out next time!
Whew! Made it! And in here, we find...
To be continued...
Double kill!
There's got to be a way to hit that invisible block...
Doy! I've got to stop taking all these stupid hits!
No! I didn't want to enter the "ruler" room again! I'll just fast-forward this part...
Whoa, careful.
However, I don't think the enemies come frequently enough to get any kind of decent kill combo... Still, it gives me muncher protection.
I think I'll take the star this time!

Oh, man. You actaully gotta get that homework done! Okay, can anyone PLEASE CONTAC HIM and I help him plaese! (I'd help, but I don't know much about drop fruits myself. We need drop fruit experts here! (What's the scientific term for a drop fruit expert?))
Nice! You can even smack the superSomeGuy712xes with the note blocks!
Demo count: 16
That last stupid superSomeGuy712x ruined my killing spree! Well, I'm still gonna eat him!
I'll just take a detour through the "ruler" room to avoid maybe one screen's worth of enemies! (Also, to collect coins, I guess.)
Alright, got my cape back...
Also, if you're really good, you can use these note blocks as weapons. Just bounce on one with good timing when an enemy is nearby to strike it!
Everything outta my way!
Hi, Yoshi!
Hey, my 1-up's getting away! Gimme my 1-up!

Oh, and by the way, these Yoshi wings can only be collected if you haven't already previously collected at least five Yoshi coins in this level. Otherwise, that Yoshi coin half won't be present, and the wings won't be available.
...a ruler! Now, we can figure out the length of things easily!
Okay, no more mister nice SomeGuy712x! Those superSomeGuy712xes aren't gonna stop me this time!
Alright, midpoint. Also, flying in this level isn't terribly useful. The screen scrolls up, but your flight plan kind of gets "logged off".
Oh, and there's this fairly easy to reach 1-up near the upper-left corner. Grab it too, even if you're already at 99 lives.
